1. Overview

Campfires are PantheonOS‚Äôs structured, multi-user conversational environments.
They transform normal group chats into:
	‚Ä¢	governed decision spaces
	‚Ä¢	live collaboration nodes
	‚Ä¢	shared memory environments
	‚Ä¢	narrative-aligned briefing circles
	‚Ä¢	daemon-supervised project engines

A Campfire is not a chatroom.
It is a RoomObject with its own:
	‚Ä¢	StateVector
	‚Ä¢	Participant graph
	‚Ä¢	Daemon loadout
	‚Ä¢	Rituals
	‚Ä¢	Logs
	‚Ä¢	Integrity chain
	‚Ä¢	Economic flows (Silk, Honey, Wax, Ember)

A Campfire is a miniature Pantheon running inside a conversation.

‚∏ª

2. Campfire Object Model

Campfire {
    id: CampfireID
    name: string
    purpose: enum {war_room, lab, family_circle, training, ritual, briefing, open_forum}
    participants: [Human | Agent]
    state: StateVector
    daemons: DaemonLoadout[]
    ledger: CampfireLog
    integrity: MerkleRoot
    rituals: RitualSet
    economy: EconomyProfile
}

2.1 StateVector

Tracked and updated continuously:

StateVector {
    tempo: float
    coherence: float
    narrative_axis: (StoryPrime[9])
    emotional_tone: float
    risk_level: float
    phase: enum {opening, flow, convergence, closing}
}


