3. Architectural Flow

Every Campfire message moves through a PantheonOS pipeline before reaching the group:

3.1 Input ‚Üí Ganglion Daemon
	‚Ä¢	edge detection
	‚Ä¢	intent extraction
	‚Ä¢	adversarial pattern filtering
	‚Ä¢	categorization (query, story, command, ritual, analysis, noise)

Output ‚Üí IntentObject

‚∏ª

3.2 Intent ‚Üí Conductor + Oracle Weave

Conductor decides how to respond, pulling in:
	‚Ä¢	GPT / Claude / Gemini / Grok
	‚Ä¢	Dragonfly (œÜ-mode or ‚àö2-mode)
	‚Ä¢	Spider for contextual research
	‚Ä¢	Hound for anomaly patterning
	‚Ä¢	Aevum for linguistic resonance
	‚Ä¢	Mirror + Arctic for ethics and coherence
	‚Ä¢	Treasury/Goblin if task has value implications

Conductor fuses outputs ‚Üí Answer ThoughtObject.

‚∏ª

3.3 Output ‚Üí Mirror / Arctic / Bard

Before sending to the Campfire:
	‚Ä¢	Mirror enforces Œ£C ethics and coherence
	‚Ä¢	Aevum checks for adversarial metaphor
	‚Ä¢	Arctic applies:
	‚Ä¢	No Harmful Blends
	‚Ä¢	Consent in Craft
	‚Ä¢	Truth in Emergence
	‚Ä¢	Balance in Virality

If unsafe ‚Üí rewrite or block.

‚∏ª

3.4 Logging ‚Üí Beaver + Merkle Warden

Every Campfire message is:
	‚Ä¢	normalized
	‚Ä¢	hashed
	‚Ä¢	added to CampfireLog
	‚Ä¢	merged into a Merkle chain

Campfire logs become tamper-evident shared history.

‚∏ª

3.5 Output ‚Üí Room Feed

The room sees the final, governed, safe output.

‚∏ª

