5. Campfire Rituals

Campfires support predefined ritual protocols that act like commands / spells:

/opening-circle

Sets:
	‚Ä¢	tempo to slow
	‚Ä¢	clears distractions
	‚Ä¢	aligns narrative axis
	‚Ä¢	engages Praus + Aion

/hellweek

Creates a 7-day structured sprint with:
	‚Ä¢	morning briefs
	‚Ä¢	evening debrief
	‚Ä¢	challenges
	‚Ä¢	metrics
	‚Ä¢	Pantheon guidance

/mirror-sieve

Run a full ethics + truth pass on a topic or decision.

/praus

Lower volatility, stabilize pacing, widen perception.

/bard-scan

Aevum checks recent messages for:
	‚Ä¢	coercive rhetoric
	‚Ä¢	adversarial metaphor
	‚Ä¢	manipulation patterns

/conductor-sync

Aligns multi-model consensus for the room.

‚∏ª

6. Shared Memory Model

Campfires maintain persistent CampfireLog objects:

CampfireLog {
    events: LogEvent[]
    merkle_root: MerkleRoot
}

Each event contains:
	‚Ä¢	message
	‚Ä¢	intent classification
	‚Ä¢	daemon decisions
	‚Ä¢	Œ£C score
	‚Ä¢	narrative vector
	‚Ä¢	artifacts created
	‚Ä¢	links to GitHub issues or docs

This is how PantheonOS turns social conversation into:
	‚Ä¢	persistent memory
	‚Ä¢	actionable plans
	‚Ä¢	reproducible decision trails
	‚Ä¢	operational doctrine

