8. Graph Architecture (Campfire-as-Circuit)

Campfires form a graph, not a list:
	‚Ä¢	nodes = Campfires
	‚Ä¢	edges = shared participants, tasks, artifacts
	‚Ä¢	flows = information, value, guidance

Pantheon can:
	‚Ä¢	route ideas between rooms
	‚Ä¢	detect bottlenecks
	‚Ä¢	identify high-value nodes
	‚Ä¢	map ‚Äúheat‚Äù and ‚Äúcurrent‚Äù within the network
	‚Ä¢	track narrative drift

This is the multi-room version of the City-as-Circuit doctrine.

